==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Trait
<hw>Trait</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F., fr. L.
<ets>tractus</ets>, fr. <ets>trahere</ets> to draw. See <er>Trace</er>,
<pos>v.</pos>, and cf. <er>Tract</er> a region, <er>Trace</er> a strap,
<er>Tret</er>.]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>A stroke; a touch.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>By this single <qex>trait</qex> Homer makes an essential
difference between the Iliad and Odyssey.</q>
<rj><qau>Broome.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A distinguishing or marked feature; a peculiarity;
<as>as, a <ex>trait</ex> of character</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><note>⟦hand⟧ Formerly pronounced <xex>tr⟦amac⟧</xex>, as in French,
and still so pronounced to some extent in England.</note>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Traiteur</ent>⟦br⟧
\'d8
